  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6836.37 sitting just above the 6834 GEX flip and massive positive gamma walls stacked from 6835-6850, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push toward the 6840-6850 zone where they hold over 38B in positive gamma exposure. The PIN regime with 96.7B total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, while the recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we just saw significant options flow that will amplify dealer hedging activity. Key levels: 6834 flip as immediate support, 6850 as the primary resistance where maximum dealer selling pressure kicks in, and 6820 as the critical negative gamma zone where dealer buying would accelerate any breakdown.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get pinned between 6835-6850 with dealers capping upside moves.",
